4. Antiviral Medication
Pregnancy is a physiological state of relative immunosup-
pression and all pregnant women should be assumed to be
at high risk and should be treated if the potential benefit
outweighs the theoretical risk of the fetus. Antiviral drugs
will help to relieve symptoms and reduce viral shedding,

Neuraminidase inhibitors are used and they are as an adjunct
to immunization. Oseltamivir is taken orally and zanamivir
is administered via inhalation. Both are category C drugs
but oseltamivir is preferred over zanamivir due to its well-
evidenced results fromclinical experience with a guaranteed
systemic absorption [9, 10]. See Table 1.
